{"TopicId":165802,"ForumId":36,"TopicTitle":"[1.3] Beta - Integrated Stack Tank Decouplers","CreatedByName":"linuxgurugamer","CreatedById":129964,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-09-24T17:47:56Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"linuxgurugamer","CreatedById":129964,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-09-24T17:47:56Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s always bothered me that you needed to add a separate part to do your staging. \u00A0It kind of makes sense if you are doing radial staging, but not for stacked.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo, I\u0027ve written this mod to fix this shortcoming.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEssentially, it adds the ability to turn on an\u00A0\u00A0integrated decoupler on all tanks which have a \u0022top\u0022 node, with some exceptions which follow:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe mod will NOT modify a tank if:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\nA tank already has a built-in decoupler\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nA tank has a built-in fairing\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nA tank has a built-in engine\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\nMost stock tanks can use this mod, some other tanks by other mods will not because of these limitations.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGenerally, the cases where a tank has a built-in engine usually means that the tank part of it isn\u0027t that significant, but there are some cases where it is, and I haven\u0027t yet decided how to deal with those.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe integrated decouplers are installed in the TOP of a tank.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTo use, build your vessel as normal, but leave off the stack decouplers. \u00A0Then, right-click on the tank where you want a decoupler, and click the button which says \u0022No decoupler\u0022. \u00A0The button will change to say \u0022Integrated Decoupler\u0022, along with the other options for a decoupler (Force Percent and Disable Staging). \u00A0The following images show a simple two stage rocket with the integrated decoupler being configured for each stage.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#e74c3c;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:16px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cu\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EThis mod requires Module Manager\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/u\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\nDownload:\u00A0\u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/linuxgurugamer/IntegratedStackDecouplers/releases\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://github.com/linuxgurugamer/IntegratedStackDecouplers/releases\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nSource: \u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/linuxgurugamer/IntegratedStackDecouplers/releases\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://github.com/linuxgurugamer/IntegratedStackDecouplers\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nLicense: GPLv3\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cs\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:16px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#e74c3c;\u0022\u003E\u003Cu\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIncompatible Mods\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/u\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/s\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cs\u003EColor Coded Canisters - due to the addition of the module \u0022ModuleJettison\u0022 to many tanks, something to do with tank shrouds\u003C/s\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDon\u0027t forget to check the staging after enabling a decoupler.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022screenshot14.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022https://image.ibb.co/c8zoPQ/screenshot14.png\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022screenshot15.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022https://image.ibb.co/gJzoPQ/screenshot15.png\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022screenshot16.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022https://image.ibb.co/dK3hjQ/screenshot16.png\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022screenshot17.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022https://image.ibb.co/dxf6B5/screenshot17.png\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022screenshot18.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022https://image.ibb.co/fXXxJk/screenshot18.png\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-10-07T14:39:32Z\u0022 title=\u002210/07/2017 02:39  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003EOctober 7, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by linuxgurugamer\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"plausse","CreatedById":64331,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-09-25T11:16:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHow elegant. Such a great idea and (in hindsight) obvious. Downloaded!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"linuxgurugamer","CreatedById":129964,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-09-30T19:59:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nUpdate, 0.0.0.2:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\nFixed issue with ModuleJettison being in part\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/linuxgurugamer/IntegratedStackDecouplers/releases/tag/0.00.2\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://github.com/linuxgurugamer/IntegratedStackDecouplers/releases/tag/0.00.2\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"linuxgurugamer","CreatedById":129964,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-10-07T15:02:52Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMod is released, here:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed1936242356\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/166246-13-integrated-stack-decouplers/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:209px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"TheKosmonaut","CreatedById":40652,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-10-07T15:23:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThread locked, per \u003Cabbr title=\u00221. Original Post(er). The first post in a thread, or the person who posted it. 2. Overpowered. A part or mechanic that upsets game balance by being too powerful.\u0022\u003EOP\u003C/abbr\u003E request. Congrats on release, \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/129964-linuxgurugamer/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022129964\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/129964-linuxgurugamer/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@linuxgurugamer\u003C/a\u003E!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}